name: NYDailyNews
text:
New York's City Council wants beaches open for swimming despite coronavirus.

“All New Yorkers, not just those wealthy enough to travel out of the city, deserve access to the beach this summer,” said Council Speaker Cory Johnson.
https://t.co/obD1NBKWyX

name: NYDailyNews
text:
The UN is warning of an increased threat of cyberattacks during the coronavirus crisis.

It is estimated that one cyberattack takes place every 39 seconds, but yet nearly 90 countries are still at the early stages of making commitments to cybersecurity.
https://t.co/TRIhRnTyq8

text:
A touring Bolivian orchestra has spent 74 days on the grounds of a German castle while 23 packs of wolves roam the surrounding woods.

The orchestra hopes to return home soon, though travel restrictions have made organizing the 6,000-mile trip complicated.
https://t.co/le4m3SDfd6

text:
Producers for "Blue Bloods" are mulling on purchasing a $125K germ-zapping robot designed to kill coronavirus.

Testing performed at the Texas Biomedical Research Institute showed the robot can snuff out 99.99% of all coronavirus in two minutes.
https://t.co/7QW6MTnzc4

text:
Trump demanded Jeff Sessions drop out of the Senate race in Alabama as bad blood boiled in the GOP primary.

“Jeff, you had your chance & you blew it," Trump wrote on Twitter. “You should drop out of the race.”
https://t.co/k2SAW4uWht
